description:
# Replace cascade body entirely with matrix dispatch — no gate, no fallback

## What changes

In src/ir_lower.rs:

Add `lower_pattern_matrix(ctx, matrix, fail_block, body_cb) -> Result`
that:
- compiles matrix via pattern_matrix::compile (.C, landed)
- walks Decision tree, emitting IR:
    Switch (TupleArity/Atom/Int/etc.) → chained Prim::TypeTest + Term::If
      (one TypeTest per case, shared across all clauses in case's subtree)
    sub-trees access projected fields via Prim::TupleField/ListHead/Tail,
      emitted ONCE at each subtree's entry, shared across leaves
    Leaf → invoke body_cb(ctx, body_id, leaf_bindings)
    PerRow → invoke existing lower_pattern_bind for that row's pattern
      (will collapse to matrix recursion in .H)
    Fail → Term::Goto(fail_block, vec![])

lower_multi_clause becomes:

```rust
fn lower_multi_clause(ctx, fn_def, param_vars, entry) -> Result {
    let fail_block = ctx.cur_mut().block(vec![]);
    // seal fail_block with Halt :function_clause (today's code)

    let matrix = build_matrix_from_clauses(fn_def, param_vars);
    ctx.cur_mut().set_terminator(entry, Term::Goto(matrix_entry, vec![]));
    lower_pattern_matrix(ctx, matrix, fail_block, |ctx, body_id, bindings| {
        let clause = &fn_def.clauses[body_id as usize];
        env_clear_and_rebind(ctx, param_vars, bindings);
        emit_param_type_guards(ctx, clause, param_vars, fail_block)?;
        if let Some(g) = &clause.guard {
            let gv = lower_expr(ctx, g, false)?;
            let body_b = ctx.cur_mut().block(vec![]);
            ctx.set_term(Term::If(gv, body_b, fail_block));
            ctx.cur_block = Some(body_b);
        }
        // .D.0 already made all bodies cont-fn-wrapped:
        let cont = mint_cont_fn(ctx, format!(\"fn_clause_{}\", body_id), clause.span);
        // ... TailCall to cont with capture_vars ...
        // ... second pass lowers cont body ...
        Ok(())
    })?;
    Ok(())
}
```

The old cascade body — ~80 LOC of try_blocks + per-clause pattern_bind +
guard + cont_fn dance — DELETED.

## What stays

- emit_param_type_guards (still emits @spec annotation tests post-bind)
- mint_cont_fn / switch_to_cont_fn / finalize_arm
- Two-pass cont-fn body lowering (outer fn fully populated first)

## What's removed

- ~80 LOC of cascade scaffolding in lower_multi_clause
- per-clause try_blocks allocation
- per-clause next:BlockId fail-chaining

## Acceptance

- ast_eval CLIF: meaningfully tighter than today (shared arity test,
  shared projection)
- All other multi-clause fixtures: meaningfully tighter OR equivalent
  (single-clause fns produce identical IR to today's
  single-pattern-bind path via 1-row matrix)
- Three-path parity for every fixture (interp/JIT/AOT outputs match)
- New unit test: matrix dispatch for ast_eval-shaped fn emits ONE
  arity-3 TypeTest, not two

## Risk

- Single-clause fns: matrix degenerates to project-then-Leaf. Emitted
  IR should be byte-identical to lower_pattern_bind's tuple branch.
  Verify; if not, fix the matrix's degenerate case.
- Multi-clause fns whose clauses share no constructor: matrix
  per-row-cascades inside the default branch, equivalent to today's
  cascade. Should be byte-identical or differ only in block ordering.
- Cont-fn capture timing: callback mints cont AFTER env rebind. mint_cont_fn
  snapshots env at call time. Verified by structure.

## NOT in this ticket

- Term::Switch (deferred — see meta)
- Multi-column matrix specialization (matrix picks col 0; future ticket
  if multi-column wins matter)
- Folding emit_param_type_guards into matrix as type-test columns
  (future ticket; today they're sequential post-bind)
